# Living changelog (since 2026-07-06)

After **any meaningful implementation, fix, live finding, or operator decision** in MEIC-with-Dash-main-V2, update:

`changes/CHANGES_SINCE_2026-07-06.md`

Do **not** create separate root-level summary docs. Deep specs stay in `changes/` (incident/design docs); the changelog is the dated index of what shipped and what we learned.

## When to update

- Code merged or behavior changed
- Live session issue or finding
- Operator decision (engine choice, rollback, deferral)
- Validation result (pytest, paper/live smoke)

## How to update

1. Add `## YYYY-MM-DD — Short title` **above** the previous entry (newest first).
2. Include: **What changed**, **Why**, **Findings/learnings**, **Tests/validation**, **Deferred**.
3. Update the **Open items** table at the bottom if status changed.
4. Link deeper docs when they exist (e.g. `STOP_MONITOR_V3_INCIDENT_*.md`, `LIVE_SESSION_*.md`).

Use the entry template at the top of the changelog file.

## Scope

- **In changelog:** everything from 2026-07-06 onward.
- **Out of changelog:** V2 rewrite history and pre-Jul-6 design — link only, do not duplicate.

## README link

`V2_README.md` links to this changelog; keep that link if the file is ever renamed (update both).
